Dear Neighbors,

I am reaching out to you this evening to share some information I have obtained regarding a recent policy change in Cary Park.  As you may or may not be aware, a letter was sent out to homeowners last week from CAS which included some information about the new pool rates.  In the middle of the back side of the page was a sentence regarding the new "Bring Your Own Beer" (BYOB) policy at the community pool unanimously approved by the Board and the Cary Park Pool Committee.

I was very concerned about this new policy and posted my concerns on our carypark.org site earlier this week.  I can not help but feel that a BYOB policy is blatantly irresponsible and negligent.  It puts the safety of our children in jeopardy and seriously questions our priorities as a community.   There were a few responses and Ken, as usual, took the time to address some concerns.  Unfortunately being told 'the lawyers think it is OK and CAS thinks it is OK so it is OK' is not OK with me so I have spent the past few days having lengthy discussions with representatives from the American Red Cross, the Wake County Department of Public Health-Environmental Services (regulates pools in Wake County) , and PPM, Inc and Omega, two of the larger property management companies in our area that represent all of our neighbors fom Amberly to Preston and dozens more.  (I have attached a list for your review.)

Bottom line, each and every individual was shocked.  They all agreed this is a dangerous policy and one that should never have been adopted.  The policy creates a substantial liability for the residents of Cary Park and degrades the integrity of this community.  Unfortunately this is just another example of poor management and decision making that has a significant impact on all of us.  Incompetence on the Board can no longer be tolerated.  We as residents need to be aware of what is going on.  These poor decisions adversely effect our property values and have a negative impact on the reputation of Cary Park.  Sadly one of the pool companies that was being considered actually turned us down due to the liability of such a policy.  This should have been a red flag.  Instead we went with a company that thinks this is OK? 

Furthermore, I have learned that PPM, Inc. has picked up six new communities since October, (including Greytone, Stonebridge, and Autumn Woods in Raleigh,) that have left CAS due to poor management and inexperience.  And we got a 25% rate increase..again approved????

Living in a community with an HOA frankly is tough.  We all have to work together and we have to make compromises and sacrifices for the best interest of the community.  Policies and changes to policies need to be seriously considered before we downgrade to such a degree.  Ironically we have downgraded so much and yet our rates keep rising...how does that work?  The Board must look at each and every decision with a broad view and recognize what is best for the entire community, not what is best for a few neighbors.  For the residents who feel a pool house bar and a BYOB are the same thing...they are not.  They are not even in the same league. I would ask you to think back when you were considering a home in Cary Park, when your realtor told you CP had a BYOB policy, what would you have thought about this community? 

Thanks for listening.  I greatly appreciate your time and hope you will share your thoughts and concerns regarding the policy change.
Sincerely,
Stacey Redgrave
