I am writing to inform you of the horrendous plight of the elderly in North Carolina.





Many North Carolinian elderly have lost their Medicaid coverage because of the increase in social security benefits that took place in Jan 09.

I am a registered nurse who works for a home care agency in Asheville NC.

My concern is for the plight of the aged and infirmed who wish to stay in their homes as long as they can.





Many elderly in their 80’s and 90’s who wish to stay in their homes were receiving Medicaid under the Medicaid “Personal Care Services” program. The

Service was provided by Home care agencies.

Under this program if the qualifying persons on Medicaid required help with activities of daily living ( bathing, dressing, mobility, incontinence, bathroom  assistance) they could receive

up to 3 hours per day assistance (60 hours per month) total. Now due to the increase in social security that occurred in Jan 09 of approx $96.40 these elderly people no longer qualify for Medicaid and have lost the only life line to caring for themselves and in many case feeding themselves as well..



The home care companies are not getting informed that coverage has changed and thus not getting paid because of this .The only way the companies knew coverage has changed is when the company gets a rejected Medicaid bill from the state of NC. This is after service has been rendered for 1 month. About $1400. 00 per month.



As a nurse I had to contact all the clients who had their Medicaid stopped and tell them they do not qualify for home aide service any more. Some of these clients made only $2.00 over the limit to disqualify them for Medicaid. They cannot afford to pay for the care out of their own pockets. There is no one to make meals no one to bathe or dress them or help them walk around transfer from their wheelchairs. All live alone without any family or friends to help. (This is a requirement of the Personal care services program that there is no one else who can perform these tasks for them.) They are going to sit in their homes and some will die.

This is taking place right now in NC.



My question is … What will the state of NC do with all of these people?. When we have to stop care because of Medicaid loss no one is there to help with their bathing dressing toileting meal prep etc.. All they want to do is live in their own homes as long as they can. This program is a heck of a lot cheaper that government sponsored care facilities.

What a shameful event.. The Feds give them a raise that many elderly do not see.. but it’s enough to push them over the limit for Medicaid thus their loss of coverage.

Personal care Services is in many states in this country and will affect 100’s of thousands of old people.



Home care agencies are not being informed that Medicaid coverage has stopped. They have provided services paying the aide for as much as a month. The only way they find out is when the Medicaid payment is refused by the program. That agency is out 1 month service provided to the tune of 1400.00. When we contact Department of Social Services they tell us the client was supposed to notify us.

Let me assure you many clients do not understand that the coverage was stopped or why. Others are so desperate they will not report it for fear of not receiving help with basic living needs. Again I repeat basic living needs.



There was reference that this may happen on the internet in 2005 but government offices were supposed to address the issues so exactly what has happened would not. I refer you to

